  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout mechanism is implemented across multiple Java source files in the apache/kafka repository (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489). The timeout is configured through SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG in CommonClientConfigs.java (line 207) and ConsumerConfig.java (line 102). On the client side, the GroupRebalanceConfig.java class stores the sessionTimeoutMs value read from the configuration (line 41). The Heartbeat.java class in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ manages the heartbeat session timeout threshold through a sessionTimer field (line 36) initialized with the sessionTimeoutMs value (line 52). The critical timeout check occurs in the HeartbeatThread.run method of AbstractCoordinator.java (lines 1513-1517), where the code checks heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now) and, if true, calls markCoordinatorUnknown() with the message 'session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response'. This detection and logging happens during the consumer polling loop's heartbeat thread. On the server side, the GroupCoordinatorConfig.java file defines CONSUMER_GROUP_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG (line 155) for the server-side consumer group session timeout configuration. The GroupMetadataManager.java file schedules consumer group session timeouts via the scheduleConsumerGroupSessionTimeout method (lines 4326-4330) which retrieves the timeout value using consumerGroupSessionTimeoutMs (lines 8464-8467). The sessionTimeoutExpired() method in Heartbeat.java (lines 119-122) checks if the sessionTimer has expired by calling sessionTimer.isExpired(). This comprehensive implementation ensures that Kafka consumers detect dropped group membership when the heartbeat session timeout expires without receiving a successful heartbeat response."
}

